[{"date": "2026-04-03T00:08:27+00:00", "title": "Wellgistics Health, Inc. (WGRX) Explores $105M Acquisition of Neuritek to Expand Healthcare Platform", "content": "We recently compiled a list of the 12 Penny Stocks with Insider Buying in 2026.\u00a0 Wellgistics Health, Inc. is one of the stocks with Insider buying in 2026.\n\nTheFly reported on March 23 that WGRX announced it had signed a non-binding, non-exclusive Letter of Intent to explore a potential all-stock acquisition of Neuritek Therapeutics, a company specializing in neuroscience research. The proposed $105 million deal, if completed, aims to expand WGRX\u2019 existing healthcare platform by integrating research capabilities alongside its technology-driven pharmacy distribution and services operations.\n\nBy combining prescription fulfillment, wholesale distribution, and AI-enabled patient access, Wellgistics Health, Inc. (NASDAQ:WGRX) seeks to better connect manufacturers, providers, and independent pharmacies nationwide. The acquisition could improve coordination between drug development and commercialization, enhance pipeline visibility, support new revenue opportunities, and create a more integrated platform to strengthen long-term shareholder value.Wellgistics Health, Inc. (WGRX) Explores $105M Acquisition of Neuritek to Expand Healthcare Platform\n\nIn a recent corporate move, on March 19, WGRX converted roughly $2 million of accrued compensation into common stock at $0.20 per share, resulting in the issuance of about 10 million shares.\n\nAlongside this, the company granted 10 million warrants exercisable at $0.01 per share with a five-year term. The conversion, approved by independent board members, reflects management\u2019s confidence in the company\u2019s strategy and aligns leadership incentives with long-term shareholder value. Newly issued shares are subject to a six-month lock-up, with customary exceptions. This transaction is designed to reinforce commitment to the company\u2019s growth while supporting alignment between executives, directors, and shareholders.\n\nWellgistics Health, Inc. (NASDAQ:WGRX) is a Tampa\u2011based healthcare and pharmaceutical logistics company offering wholesale distribution, prescription fulfillment, technology\u2011enabled pharmacy services, and clinical support to independent pharmacies and manufacturers.\n\nWhile we acknowledge the potential of WGRX as an investment, we believe certain AI stocks offer greater upside potential and carry less downside risk. If you're looking for an extremely undervalued AI stock that also stands to benefit significantly from Trump-era tariffs and the onshoring trend, see our free report on the best short-term AI stock.\n\nREAD NEXT: 33 Stocks That Should Double in 3 Years and 15 Stocks That Will Make You Rich in 10 Years\n\nDisclosure: None. Follow Insider Monkey on Google News.\n\nView Comments", "link": "https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/healthcare/articles/wellgistics-health-inc-wgrx-explores-000827173.html", "symbols": ["WGRX.US"], "tags": ["HEALTHCARE", "M-A", "PHARMA", "SHAREHOLDER"], "sentiment": {"polarity": 0.996, "neg": 0.009, "neu": 0.814, "pos": 0.177}}, {"date": "2026-03-12T14:30:35+00:00", "title": "BC-Most Active Stocks", "content": "NEW YORK (AP) \u2014 prices for the Nasdaq composite, NYSE and NYSE American listed most active stocks.\n\nNasdaq most active stocks:\n\nStock Name Volume High Low Last Change Eightco Holdings Inc. 112,077,996 1.10 0.886 0.924 +0.1151 Wellgistics Health Inc. 52,525,540 0.2099 0.1762 0.1811 -0.0107 Decent Holding Inc. 52,436,885 0.2999 0.264 0.2701 -0.172 XCF Global Inc. 32,357,565 0.65 0.5192 0.5749 +0.0767 NVIDIA Corp. 31,982,210 184.86 182.05 183.1761 -2.8539 Ondas Inc. 31,466,096 10.40 9.85 10.27 +0.44 Agape ATP Corporation 28,522,443 6.30 5.01 5.3997 +1.2297 Codexis Inc. 28,147,519 2.13 1.685 1.7399 +0.4699 Polar Power Inc. 26,681,283 2.39 2.13 2.3301 +0.3901 Lunai Bioworks Inc. 22,086,789 0.163 0.1513 0.1585 -0.0316 Mobix Labs Inc. 19,314,